Šimon Ornest said: "In concert, we want to collect positive energy."
What do you think of the fact that in less than a month it should be the end of the world?
It's just one of those alarming news, the kind of traps we like to fall into.
In our band The Tap Tap, we laugh about it and we think we're the only group able to collect a positive amount of energy in order to push back or prevent the end of the world.
In addition, in December, you set up a very unique project: three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you present this project in more detail to our readers?
It's a charity we've been preparing for two years.
We decided to use the marketing potential of the end of the Maya calendar announced for 21 December at 11.10 a.m.
The day before, on 20 December, three concerts will take place simultaneously, in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end almost at the end of the Maya calendar on Kiribati Island, which is in the Pacific Ocean, on a time zone 12 hours ahead of us.
Who had that idea?
At first I think it was my idea, then we designed everything with our creator, Honza Augusta.
Apart from the fact that we want to collect enough positive energy to save the world, we also want, together with the public, to reflect on the state of the world that we leave to our children.
At the end of the Maya calendar, we created a collection of unique objects, including shoes, T-shirts, bags, and original keys against the end of the world, by buying them online at www.e-tap.cz people can also support us.
The Tap Tap group with other performers also recorded a hymn against the end of the world entitled "End of the World Cancelled" (in Czech "Konec světa zrušeno").
It is already very popular on YouTube, will we hear it also at these charity concerts?
Of course, all at the end, finally, if we succeed and the end of the world doesn't happen...
It will be sung simultaneously by all the performers in the three concerts.
The hymns will also meet at some point on a very unique live Czech television show.
The lyrics of this song were written by Tomáš Hanák, who also plays the main role of Jesus in the video, Xindl X also sings there...
How did you come to cooperate with them?
We collaborate with other Czech show-biz personalities, due to the fact that we organize numerous concerts and charitable events...
We are working to involve them intensively in these projects.
It turned out that most of them are interested in such cooperation and that it amuses them.
What will be the benefits of these concerts against the end of the world?
To equip the Studeo training centre which is accessible to people with reduced mobility and which we have been working on in the framework of the Jedlička institute, with the association Tap, and this for six years.
Teachers regularly visit the students of the Jedličkřv Institute and offer them activities that interest and entertain them.
The students themselves cannot afford to go to classes, we try to help them in this way.
As part of the completion of the construction of the Jedlička Institute, we will transfer this project to a new independent building.
Will there be several music bands and performers on stage at each of these concerts?
By what criteria, did you choose them?
We have tried to develop a program for all generations, including children.
For example, in Prague, will go on stage Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý.
All details can be found at www.kpks.cz.
