But pity is totally useless, because people with disabilities are not suffering beings, abandoned by all, whom we must take in pity.
They are people who can live a life in their own right and flourish, provided they have the necessary means, of course.
I often say that when people with disabilities achieve something, it is not just a step forward for them but for the whole of society.
