There are many gaps between health programmes and the ordinary citizen, says Ricardo Salazar, a journalist from Guadalajara who has embraced the cause of HIV.
And the biggest thing is prevention.
In all places dedicated to this, "we have actually increased the distribution of condoms, before we were given one or two, now we are given packets of 100, it is very good, but as a result, still today, some do not have access to condoms," he says.
Adolescents are among the most vulnerable to new infections.
The question, "What are you going to do with it?," put up with sarcasm and value judgments by social workers, guidance counsellors, pharmacists and health professionals, is the question that teenagers don't want to hear, says the journalist.
He proposed that this inefficient distribution be redirected; that condoms not only be sold at counters, but be found in public toilet dispensers and in places frequented by young people.
It's not about encouraging promiscuity.
Nor was it a question of paying them the girls and the motel, as Governor Emilio González had replied when asked if there would be a distribution of condoms within his administration.
"It's not how sexuality works, it's best to provide condoms to people who are already sexually active," he said.
Figures in Jalisco
There are 13,435 cumulative cases (12,158 AIDS cases and 1,317 HIV cases).
The State is the fourth largest State in the country in terms of the number of new and cumulative AIDS cases and 13th in terms of the number of HIV patients.
92% of infections occur by sexual route, 6% by blood route and 2% by perinatal route.
It is estimated that 50,000 people live with HIV, since for each case registered, there are 4 or 5 people who do not know about it.
A judgment ratified on appeal by a United States court ignores the restructuring of the Vitro group's debt through a commercial bankruptcy in Mexico. The scenario causes a bad precedent for all domestic companies with branches in the neighbouring country and with solvency problems.
It therefore seems that the procedures for the survival of companies authorized by Mexican laws are not valid in the country at the star banner, contrary to international agreements.
