However, the resolution will allow the leading glass manufacturer in Mexico to appeal to the Supreme Court of the United States on the basis of three inconsistencies.
First, while the trial judge points out that creditors must register under the United States Bankruptcy Act, the Fifth Circuit Appeal Court, based in New Orleans, states that the main proceeding is formal commercial bankruptcy in Mexico.
The first point would involve denouncing cooperation in cross-border proceedings in insolvency cases involving companies with a cross-border profile.
Indeed, the United Nations Model Law for the Uniformity of International Commercial Law had been created for that purpose by taking the American Law Institute as the arbitrator.
